\layout Standard

These options include the sizes and the positions of all windows, the texts
 of all prompts, the positions of splitters in the main program window and
 the other folder views as well as several other things.
 These options are special in that they do not appear in the options dialog
 and so can not be changed directly - instead Mahogany remembers them each
 time it is shut down, so when it is reopened it will be in exactly the
 same state as during the last run.
 Try to play with it: adjust the sizes of the main program window and the
 splitters in it as you like, exit Mahogany and restart it (this is for
 testing only, of course, you do not need to do it each time!) - you should
 see that the window reappears on the same position (although this might
 not work under some window managers), has the same size and is split in
 the same manner.
